article.headline: N. Colorado 30, Idaho St. 7
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- Quarterback Bryan Waggener completed 24 of 42 attempts for 212 yards and a touchdown, as well as rushed for another score, on Saturday as Northern Colorado beat Idaho State 30-7. Alex Thompson had nine catches for 75 yards and a touchdown for the Bears (2-5, 1-4 Big Sky), and teammate Patrick Walker made nine for 89 yards. Tailback Andre Harris gained 113 yards on 24 carries and scored a touchdown. Northern Colorado racked up 435 yards total offense, while holding Idaho State (0-7, 0-4) to 197 yards. The Bengals had minus-11 yards rushing for the game. Bengal quarterback Russel Hill completed 29 of 49 attempts for 208 yards and a touchdown. His top target was wide receiver Jaron Taylor who had seven catches for 42 yards and a touchdown. Idaho State's linebackers A.J. Storm and Phillip Arias had 14 tackles and 11 tackles, respectively.
